Patch Set 4:

AFAIK, this was kept purposefully by design to match with glance-direct flow so that user can use same image id to stage and import data using glance-direct method and if not that data will be cleared while deleting the image.

But if everyone agrees I would say this will be good option to have to.

Patch Set 4:

> AFAIK, this was kept purposefully by design to match with
 > glance-direct flow so that user can use same image id to stage and
 > import data using glance-direct method and if not that data will be
 > cleared while deleting the image.
 > 
 > But if everyone agrees I would say this will be good option to have
 > to.

Well, I think the staging thing is a little awkward to begin with, so I definitely understand the desire to clear it. However, I think consistency is good, and making direct and download behave the same is ideal. So, I tend to agree that we should just leave it.
